50|$|A {{number of}} {{offshore}} jurisdictions promote {{the incorporation of}} captive insurance companies within the jurisdiction to allow the sponsor to manage risk. In more sophisticated offshore insurance markets, onshore insurance companies can also establish an offshore subsidiary in the jurisdiction to <b>reinsure</b> certain risks underwritten by the onshore parent, and thereby reduce overall reserve and capital requirements. Onshore reinsurance companies may also incorporate an offshore subsidiary to <b>reinsure</b> catastrophic risks.|$|R
