50|$|The IRS {{defines a}} PCC {{as a legal}} entity formed by a Sponsoring Organization under the laws of a {{specific}} domicile. Under the statute of a given state domicile then entity may be organized under a corporate or unincorporated entity statute. The assets of each cell are segregated from the assets of any other cell. The cell may issue insurance or annuity contracts, <b>reinsure</b> such contracts, or facilitate the securitization of obligations of a sponsoring insurance company.|$|R
